# .retireignore
#
# Suppress known false positives or accepted-risk findings.
# Format (one rule per line):
#
#   [component]           — suppress all findings for this package
#   [component] [version] — suppress a specific version
#   [CVE-ID]              — suppress a specific CVE across all packages
#
# Each suppression MUST be reviewed and re-evaluated each quarter.
# Add a comment above every entry explaining why it is suppressed.
#
# Example:
#
# lodash 4.17.20
# CVE-2021-23337: accepted risk — no user input reaches the merge path in this project
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add your suppressions below this line.
# Start empty — let RetireJS surface all findings on the first run,
# then suppress only those that are genuinely not applicable.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
